<h4 class="mt-7 mb-3 text-xl leading-8 font-extrabold font-header tracking-tight text-blue-600 sm:text-2xl">Postponing: Journalism &amp; Academia</h4>
<p>Although I am interested in bringing contextual citations to <strong>Journalism</strong> and <strong>Academicia</strong>, I expect it will take time to:</p>
<ul class="disc">
  <li>convince the editors to use CiteIt</li>
  <li>get the tech people to incorporate CiteIt in their publishing software</li>
  <li>teach the journalists/academics to create contextual citations</li>
</ul>
<br /><br />

<p>CiteIt's current <strong class="text-blue-600">stratgey</strong> is to <strong class="text-blue-600">convert Wikipedia to contextual citations</strong> as a showcase of what's possible.
The plan is to expand CiteIt to journalism and academia later, as interest and resources become available.</p>
